The death toll in the floods in KwaZulu-Natal has risen to 259. Scores of people are still missing. Floods have destroyed homes leaving thousands of people homeless. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has described the scenes in KwaZulu-Natal as catastrophic. Floods have destroyed homes leaving thousands of people homeless. At least 259 people have died in the floods. The president visited some of the affected areas on Wednesday. WATCH | Floods wreak havoc in Durban Ramaphosa says government is making preparations to declare the province a state of disaster. "The bridges have collapsed, the roads have collapsed, people have died, our people are injured so this is a catastrophe of enormous proportions," he said. 